'''Eszter Bánffy''', {{Post-nominals|country=GBR|size=100%|sep=,|FSA|FBA}} (born 1957) is a Hungarian [[prehistorian]], [[archaeologist]], and academic. Since 2013, she has been Director of the Romano-Germanic Commission at the [[German Archaeological Institute]]. She is also a [[professor]] at the Archaeological Institute of the [[Hungarian Academy of Sciences]].<ref name="FBA">{{cite web|title=Professor Dr Dr H.c. Eszter Bánffy|url=https://www.britac.ac.uk/users/professor-dr-dr-hc-eszter-b%C3%A1nffy|website=British Academy|accessdate=8 September 2017}}</ref><ref name="dainst">{{cite web|title=Prof. Dr. Eszter Bánffy|url=https://www.dainst.org/mitarbeiter-detailansicht/-/person-display/141867|website=Deutsches Archäologisches Institut|accessdate=8 September 2017}}</ref><ref name="guest">{{cite web|title=Prof. Dr. Eszter Bánffy DSc, guest professor|url=http://www.oslenytan.hu/index.php/en/staff/169-prof-dr-eszter-banffy-dsc-guest-professor|website=Őslénytan|accessdate=8 September 2017}}</ref>

==Honours==
On 9 April 2015, Bánffy was elected a [[Fellow of the Society of Antiquaries of London]].<ref name="FSA">{{cite web|title=Fellows Directory: Banffy|url=https://www.sal.org.uk/about-us/fellows-directory/?fs=Banffy+&page=1|website=Society of Antiquaries of London|accessdate=8 September 2017}}</ref> In 2017, she was elected a [[Corresponding Fellow of the British Academy]] (FBA), the United Kingdom's [[national academy]] for the humanities and social sciences.<ref name="FBA" /> She is also an elected [[Member of the European Academy of Sciences and Arts]].<ref name="guest" /><ref>{{cite web|title=Members|url=http://www.euro-acad.eu/members-by-country/|website=European Academy of Sciences and Arts|accessdate=8 September 2017}}</ref>

