The '''''Indian Journal of Asian Affairs''''' is a biannual [[peer-reviewed]] [[academic journal]] that covers current and contemporary Asian affairs, including foreign policy, defense, security, peace, conflict and development. Devoted to an objective analysis of important contemporary and current Asian affairs, it covers theoretical, empirical, historical and policy issues from a wide range of perspectives and critical appraisals within a multidisciplinary framework. Its Editorial Team includes [[BM Jain]], [[Sumit Ganguly]], [[Patrick James (professor)|Patrick James]], [[Kevin P. Clements]] and [[T.V. Paul]].

